# T27 — SSOT-MATH (constitutional rule)

## Source of truth

- All **mathematics, physics, constants, formulas, and verification tests** live in **`*.t27`** and are run through **`tri` / `t27c`**.
- Pipeline steps should record experience in **`.trinity/experience/`** (jsonl / project schema) when applicable.

## Prohibitions

- **Do not add** new Python (or other scripting) on the **critical path** (verdict, conformance, assurance scenarios) if the same can be expressed in t27 + tri.
- **Do not duplicate** formulas in README/Markdown without pointing to the canonical `.t27` spec.

## Exceptions (legacy)

- Existing Python (`conformance/kepler_newton_tests.py`, `clara-bridge/run_scenario.py`, `clara-bridge/tests/*.py`) is **legacy**; **do not** add new features there. Migrate per **`docs/TZ-T27-001-NO-PYTHON-CRITICAL-PATH.md`**.

## Conflict resolution

- `.t27` specs, `docs/T27-CONSTITUTION.md`, `docs/TDD-CONTRACT.md`, and `docs/NUMERIC-STANDARD-001.md` override ad-hoc scripts.

## Language (English)

- **First-party** Markdown (`docs/`, `specs/**/*.md`, `architecture/`, `clara-bridge/`, `conformance/`, root `README.md` / `AGENTS.md` / `CLAUDE.md` / `task.md` / `SOUL.md`) **must be English**. No new Cyrillic; legacy paths only in **`docs/.legacy-non-english-docs`**.
- **Source** (`.t27`, `.zig`, …): English comments/identifiers, ASCII per ADR-004.

## Required reading after clone

After `CLAUDE.md`, read **`docs/T27-CONSTITUTION.md`** (SSOT-MATH + LANG-EN).
